File: In the short clip, Babes can be heard mocking Lady Zamar while zooming in to show the acne on her face. JOHANNESBURG - Bongekile Simelane, better known as Babes Wodumo, claims her Twitter account has been hacked. In a video posted on Instagram, Babes said someone had managed to hack into her account and is using it to post offensive content that does not come from her. READ: Babes Wodumo dragged for insulting Lady Zamar She also posted a screenshot of a message that the "person" sent to her on WhatsApp with the caption: "Guys akumina who’s posting ku Twitter." Babes came under fire on Thursday after a video of her making fun of Lady Zamar's acne went viral on social media. Guys akumina who’s posting ku Twitter A post shared by  Bongekile Simelane (@babes_wodumo) on Aug 14, 2019 at 11:16pm PDT Guys akumina who’s posting ku Twitter A post shared by  Bongekile Simelane (@babes_wodumo) on Aug 14, 2019 at 11:21pm PDT